main event: A military unit sighted a cigar-shaped object with windows flying to the northeast at an estimated altitude of 15,000 feet for approximately 25 minutes.
interesting points: The object emitted a bluish-white light from a window at its lower end., The object was described as being 25-30 feet in diameter and cigar-shaped., Multiple military units were involved in observing the object., The report concluded that the object was likely a balloon due to insufficient data., The sighting lasted for about 25 minutes.
